    "created_at": "2015-02-26T10:04:01Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-02-26T10:04:26Z",
    "body": "It's kind of a gotcha, but you're explicitly giving a mutable ref of your iterator to another object, so it's completely natural.\n\nWhat has been proposed before is a peeking version of take_while that can only be used on .peekable, that way you could use both take_while and still access the boundary iterator element afterwards.\n",
